					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section class="projects" id="projects">
				<h2>Projects</h2>
				<div class="grid">
					<ProjectCard
						title="Mums Filibabba"
						description="An ongoing recipe website project to collect and share recipes of friends and family."
						techStack="MERN stack, JavaScript, CSS. Formik + yup for form handling and validation. Axios and React Query for API requests and state management. Bcrypt and Jsonwebtoken for authentication."
						cardColor="#DFF2A7"
						githubUrl="https://github.com/Snoira/recept_webpage"
					/>
					<ProjectCard
						title="YAY BNB"
						description="A modern Airbnb-inspired booking platform with responsive design and TypeScript for enhanced type safety."
						techStack="Next.js, TypeScript, TailwindCSS + Shadcn UI. Utilizes Prisma for database management. Zod for type validation."
						githubUrl="https://github.com/Snoira/Airbnb-project"
					/>
					<ProjectCard
						title="Portfolio Website"
						description="A personal portfolio built with Astro for showcasing my work."
						techStack="Astro, CSS, TypeScript, Netlify."
						cardColor="#EA8C55"
						githubUrl="https://github.com/Snoira/webdev-portfolio"
					/>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section class="about" id="about">
				<!-- <div class="about-content"> -->
				<div class="about-text">
					<h2>About Me</h2>
					<p>
						I&#39;m a junior full-stack JavaScript developer. I
						recently graduated from Nackademin&#39;s Fullstack Web
						Development program, which concluded with a six-month
						internship at Funnel.
						<!-- <br /><br /> -->
						<!-- Before becoming a developer, I set out to tackle global issues
						by studying Environmental Science, including biology and
						geography. Eventually, I realized I preferred solving smaller,
						more hands-on problems in code, as well as the collaborative
						nature of being a developer, which led me to change direction. -->
						<br /><br />
						Other than coding, I've also found an interest in web design
						and user experience (UX). I'm excited to explore this further
						and incorporate design principles into my development work.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image-container">
					<Image
						src={portrait_outside}
						alt="Portrait of Nora outside"
						class="about-image"
					/>
				</div>
				<!-- </div> -->
			</section>
			<section class="contact" id="contact">
				<h2>Contact Me</h2>
				<p>
					Feel free to reach out if you have any questions or would
					like to connect!
				</p>
				<form class="contact-form" data-netlify="true">
					<input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="contact" />
					<div>
						<label for="name">Name:</label>
						<input type="text" id="name" name="name" required />
					</div>
					<div>
						<label for="email">Email:</label>
						<input type="email" id="email" name="email" required />
					</div>
					<div>
						<label for="message">Message:</label>
						<textarea id="message" name="message" required
						></textarea>
					</div>
					<button type="submit">Send</button>
				</form>
			</section>
